{
  "stem": "7506.5",
  "chunk_idx": 6,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "She would drink a bit of water.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "I would sit next to her bunk trying to feed her the soup.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And she would say to me, I-- you eat it.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "[PAUSES] And I have a big problem with that to this day.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "Psychologically, I have a big problem with that.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And I know it's unfounded that I should have the problem, because it's not logical.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "I have the problem of I eat the soup which she refused to eat.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "[PAUSES] And in a kind of crazy meshuggeneh way, I say to myself, that's why-- what happened to her is because I ate her soup.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "I know, logically speaking, that is not so.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "And I don't say that to convince myself of that.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "I know that is logically not so.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "But when I think and see myself in my mind's eye sitting next to the bunk feeding my poor sister the food, which she just couldn't eat it.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "She couldn't get it down the throat.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "I could still eat, although I'd lost a lot of weight because of the typhus.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "The lack of food, the lack of proper food-- vegetables, fruit, was nonexistent-- I had deteriorated physically, although I was still up and about, so to speak.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "[PAUSES] That time in the camp when we were outside of the barracks, there were an awful lot of people-- corpses.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "The barrack we were was amongst other barracks, and it seemed to me that every morning, people would take dead people out of the barracks and put them outside.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "Like, lay them down.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So in the beginning of 1945, after being separated from my mother and my father, the barracks around us all had, like, heaps of bodies.",
      "word_count": 25
    }
  ],
